result.name: Korean BBQ TIME

reviews.text: I think this restaurant is one of the most unique place for korean cuisine. From the naming, we may learn that it offers roasting beef or pork. Besides, it is displaying many of posters issued early 1960 or 1970. And they have a menu named lunch box, that causes many old ages recall memories of their youth. It was still very good.

The restaurant was crowded. The food was super quick. The service was okay. 

Went there for lunch and had their lunch set. The beef contained 85%fat and 15% meat. You can see the visible fat I tried to extract from the lunch. Can't say about the other menu. 

Two star for the service and the cheap lunch. Drink included.
Very enjoyable BBQ... with good choices.. do have the Bibimbap rice too

Pretty Authentic Korean BBQ & A La Carte Food in Tung Chung!

Setting: 
Easy to find in the corner of Fu Tung Centre.
All tables are equipped with BBQ and Hotpot cooking facilities with an extractor fan above each table. The decor is post WW2 retro style, very quirky and appealing.

Food Selection on Menu: 
Very extensive selection for BBQ— red meats, veg and especially seafood
Also good selection for A La carte sets:
Starters: Korean pizza, Bimbap etc 
Main dishes: Korean Glass Noddles, Bibimbap, Retro Pickled Onion and Pork Rice etc

A meal of 3 my family and I ordered for an evening meal include: BBQ session with 3 types of meat (beef, pork, 6 capelin), selection of mushrooms, sweet potato, complementary pickled Vegs, Egg, and sweet corn, plus a retro Korean style lunchbox with seasoned beef and spam rice and 2 drinks.
Food are delicious, but do notify your preference on the fat & meat ratio :)

Portion: BBQ portion is negotiable as it depends on what you order and how many ingredients you order.
The lunchbox from the a la carte is plentiful for one to finish; and it’s ideal to share with BBQ.

Customer Service: Staff speaks English, Korean and Chinese. There a lot of staff during our visit so it’s easy to catch their attention to make an order/request. 

Cost: $150/person for BBQ

Will definitely recommend!
Very expensive and unattractive ambience. Food was OK, nothing special.

reviews.text: 口味很棒的韓式料理👍
好好味😋
座位很舒適，沒有一般香港餐廳的緊迫感。石鍋拌飯很好吃，溫度很夠不會吃到一半就冷掉。炒飯是現場桌邊炒的，覺得可能是追求鍋巴口感的關係，炒飯口感都是硬硬的，口味也是覺得鹹，但是搭配炒飯的起司蛋很好吃。烤肉方面豬肉很不錯，鍋邊的玉米甜的有些不科學。湯麵媽媽吃了覺得湯頭很好。整體來說很棒，會想再回訪的店。對了，有個缺點是...吃燒烤陪的是不冰的可樂...是常溫的QQ
他的套餐不太值得吃，反而石頭煱飯，韓麵不錯
The meat is just delicious, bring a thin jacket as the place is super cold. The prize is more than just and you really should try several meat!
